---
/**
 * Germany FAQ Accordion section — modern Astro component
 * Outlines the 6 critical CFO and Head of Tax questions with smooth accordion expand/collapse transitions.
 */
---

<section class="faq-section bg-[#FAFBFD] py-20 lg:py-24 border-t border-gray-100" id="faq">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px] px-6">
    
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <div class="text-xs lg:text-sm font-bold text-[#0057FF] uppercase tracking-widest mb-3 font-head">CFO & Head of Tax FAQ</div>
      <h2 class="text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-extrabold text-[#0A0F1E] tracking-tight mb-4 font-head">
        Six questions we hear in every first call
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base text-gray-500 leading-relaxed max-w-[620px] mx-auto">
        Direct answers. No marketing language. If a question isn't on this list, ask it on the briefing.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Accordion List -->
    <div class="faq-list space-y-4" data-faq-accordion>
      
      <!-- Item 1 -->
      <div class="faq-item bg-white border border-gray-200/80 rounded-xl overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300 hover:border-[#0057FF]/35">
        <button class="faq-q w-full text-left px-6 py-5 flex justify-between items-center gap-4 font-bold text-sm lg:text-base text-[#0A0F1E] font-head cursor-pointer bg-transparent border-0 outline-none" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Is ViDA actually law yet? Or is this an early-mover argument?</span>
          <span class="faq-icon text-[#0057FF] text-xl font-normal transition-transform duration-200 shrink-0 select-none">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a max-h-0 overflow-hidden transition-[max-height] duration-300 ease-in-out">
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 pt-1 text-sm lg:text-base text-gray-500 leading-relaxed border-t border-gray-50">
            ViDA was <strong>formally adopted by the EU Council on 11 March 2025</strong> as Council Directive (EU) 2025/516. Phase 1 implementation deadline is 1 July 2030 for cross-border DRR and the Peppol-based digital invoicing framework. This is not speculative — it is binding EU law with a published timetable. Member states are now in transposition. Validate the directive text on EUR-Lex; the dates below it match what we're showing.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Item 2 -->
      <div class="faq-item bg-white border border-gray-200/80 rounded-xl overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300 hover:border-[#0057FF]/35">
        <button class="faq-q w-full text-left px-6 py-5 flex justify-between items-center gap-4 font-bold text-sm lg:text-base text-[#0A0F1E] font-head cursor-pointer bg-transparent border-0 outline-none" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>We have a 2027-only project already approved. Should we tear it up?</span>
          <span class="faq-icon text-[#0057FF] text-xl font-normal transition-transform duration-200 shrink-0 select-none">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a max-h-0 overflow-hidden transition-[max-height] duration-300 ease-in-out">
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 pt-1 text-sm lg:text-base text-gray-500 leading-relaxed border-t border-gray-50">
            Not necessarily. Two honest paths: <strong>(a) ship the 2027 project as planned</strong> and run a parallel ViDA evaluation in 2028, accepting you'll likely re-platform; or <strong>(b) pause the 2027 RFP for six weeks</strong> and re-scope it as a ViDA-ready selection. Path (b) typically adds 8–10% to the 2027 budget and removes the 2029 re-platform line. We don't recommend (a) when total programme spend over five years is the metric — but we don't have your numbers. Bring them to the briefing and we'll model both honestly.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Item 3 -->
      <div class="faq-item bg-white border border-gray-200/80 rounded-xl overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300 hover:border-[#0057FF]/35">
        <button class="faq-q w-full text-left px-6 py-5 flex justify-between items-center gap-4 font-bold text-sm lg:text-base text-[#0A0F1E] font-head cursor-pointer bg-transparent border-0 outline-none" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Does the platform actually post into our SAP without changes?</span>
          <span class="faq-icon text-[#0057FF] text-xl font-normal transition-transform duration-200 shrink-0 select-none">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a max-h-0 overflow-hidden transition-[max-height] duration-300 ease-in-out">
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 pt-1 text-sm lg:text-base text-gray-500 leading-relaxed border-t border-gray-50">
            Yes — and this is the question we hear most. The ClearTax SAP add-on is <strong>certified on SAP Store</strong> for both S/4HANA and ECC. It posts to your existing chart of accounts using standard BAPIs. <strong>No changes to your COA, no changes to your close calendar, no ABAP changes.</strong> The typical integration in production is 4–8 weeks. Your auditor sees the same general ledger entries they see today.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Item 4 -->
      <div class="faq-item bg-white border border-gray-200/80 rounded-xl overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300 hover:border-[#0057FF]/35">
        <button class="faq-q w-full text-left px-6 py-5 flex justify-between items-center gap-4 font-bold text-sm lg:text-base text-[#0A0F1E] font-head cursor-pointer bg-transparent border-0 outline-none" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What about GoBD and the Betriebsprüfung specifically?</span>
          <span class="faq-icon text-[#0057FF] text-xl font-normal transition-transform duration-200 shrink-0 select-none">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a max-h-0 overflow-hidden transition-[max-height] duration-300 ease-in-out">
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 pt-1 text-sm lg:text-base text-gray-500 leading-relaxed border-t border-gray-50">
            The archive is <strong>GoBD-compliant with 10-year immutable retention</strong>. Every state change on every invoice is timestamp-logged with cryptographic integrity. The exception command centre exposes a "tax audit view" that walks a Betriebsprüfung auditor through the trail in the order they'll ask for it. Several of our customers have completed Bundeszentralamt audits using exactly this view. We can put you in touch with one as a reference.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Item 5 -->
      <div class="faq-item bg-white border border-gray-200/80 rounded-xl overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300 hover:border-[#0057FF]/35">
        <button class="faq-q w-full text-left px-6 py-5 flex justify-between items-center gap-4 font-bold text-sm lg:text-base text-[#0A0F1E] font-head cursor-pointer bg-transparent border-0 outline-none" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Can we run a pilot? What does a 90-day proof look like?</span>
          <span class="faq-icon text-[#0057FF] text-xl font-normal transition-transform duration-200 shrink-0 select-none">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a max-h-0 overflow-hidden transition-[max-height] duration-300 ease-in-out">
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 pt-1 text-sm lg:text-base text-gray-500 leading-relaxed border-t border-gray-50">
            Standard 90-day pilot scope: <strong>one legal entity, one ERP, one process flow</strong> (typically AR for the issue mandate). We bring a Frankfurt-based delivery lead and a tax tech consultant; you provide a finance owner and an IT contact. End-of-pilot deliverable is a production-ready integration plus a written report on what would change for the full rollout. Pricing is fixed; success criteria are agreed in week one.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Item 6 -->
      <div class="faq-item bg-white border border-gray-200/80 rounded-xl overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300 hover:border-[#0057FF]/35">
        <button class="faq-q w-full text-left px-6 py-5 flex justify-between items-center gap-4 font-bold text-sm lg:text-base text-[#0A0F1E] font-head cursor-pointer bg-transparent border-0 outline-none" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>How is pricing structured? Per invoice, per entity, per seat?</span>
          <span class="faq-icon text-[#0057FF] text-xl font-normal transition-transform duration-200 shrink-0 select-none">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a max-h-0 overflow-hidden transition-[max-height] duration-300 ease-in-out">
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 pt-1 text-sm lg:text-base text-gray-500 leading-relaxed border-t border-gray-50">
            Honestly: it depends. For most German enterprises in our customer base it's an <strong>annual platform subscription</strong> with usage tiers by invoice volume, plus a one-time implementation fee. We do not charge per seat. We do not charge for additional country mandates added later. <strong>If you're at 100k+ annual invoices, we'll quote on the briefing.</strong> If you're under, you'll likely fit a standard tier without bespoke pricing.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<script is:inline>
  (() => {
    const list = document.querySelector('[data-faq-accordion]');
    if (!list) return;
    const triggers = list.querySelectorAll('.faq-q');
    
    triggers.forEach(q => {
      q.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const item = q.closest('.faq-item');
        const content = item.querySelector('.faq-a');
        const icon = q.querySelector('.faq-icon');
        const isOpen = item.classList.contains('open');

        // Close all other accordion items
        list.querySelectorAll('.faq-item').forEach(i => {
          if (i !== item) {
            i.classList.remove('open');
            const otherBtn = i.querySelector('.faq-q');
            const otherContent = i.querySelector('.faq-a');
            const otherIcon = i.querySelector('.faq-icon');
            if (otherBtn) otherBtn.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
            if (otherContent) otherContent.style.maxHeight = '0px';
            if (otherIcon) {
              otherIcon.textContent = '+';
              otherIcon.style.transform = '';
            }
          }
        });

        // Toggle selected accordion item
        if (isOpen) {
          item.classList.remove('open');
          q.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
          content.style.maxHeight = '0px';
          if (icon) {
            icon.textContent = '+';
            icon.style.transform = '';
          }
        } else {
          item.classList.add('open');
          q.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'true');
          content.style.maxHeight = content.scrollHeight + 'px';
          if (icon) {
            icon.textContent = '−';
            icon.style.transform = 'rotate(180deg)';
          }
        }
      });
    });
  })();
</script>
